# Vue 3 & Nuxt

## Composition API
- Use `setup()` (or `<script setup>`) for component logic; use `ref` and `reactive` for reactive state.
- Use `computed()` for derived state; use `watch` and `watchEffect` for side effects.
- Use lifecycle hooks: `onMounted`, `onUpdated`, etc.; use `provide`/`inject` for dependency injection.

## Project Structure
- Typical layout: `src/components/`, `composables/`, `views/`, `router/`, `store/`, `assets/`; `App.vue`, `main.js` (or Nuxt `app/`, `pages/`, `components/`).

## Best Practices
- Use TypeScript for type safety; define props and emits; use Vue 3 style guide and naming conventions.
- Use `Teleport` when needed; use `Suspense` for async components; use Vite for dev and build.
- In Nuxt: use file-based routing, `useAsyncData`/`useFetch` for data, auto-imports for components and composables.
